4 Section 4. Section 39-11-404, MCA, is amended to read:
5 "39-11-404. (Temporary) Employer job growth incentive tax credit -- administration. (1) An
6 employer that hires qualifying new employees is eligible for an annual job growth incentive tax credit against
7 income taxes imposed pursuant to Title 15, chapter 30 or 31.
8 (2) The amount and duration of the credit is administered by the department of revenue as
9 provided in 15-30-2361 and 15-31-175.
10 (3) A qualifying employer seeking approval to claim a credit shall apply for a credit certificate with
11 the department for the preceding calendar year. The application must be submitted on a form prescribed by the
12 department on which the employer:
13 (a) identifies and describes the number of qualifying new employees hired;
14 (b) provides necessary details to calculate the net employee growth and qualifying net employee
15 growth;
16 (c) provides documentation necessary to calculate the job growth incentive tax credit, including but
17 not limited to the average yearly wage of each qualifying new employee; and
18 (d) submits any other information the department considers necessary for auditing purposes and to
19 determine whether the employer qualifies for a credit certificate.
20 (4) After receiving an application, the department shall:
21 (a) provide the employer with a credit certificate, which must accompany the employer's tax return
22 that is filed with the department of revenue; or
23 (b) deny an application for a credit certificate and provide the employer with the reasoning for the
24 denial. Prior to issuing a denial, the department shall provide the employer with an opportunity to resolve
25 deficiencies in the application.
26 (5) The department shall provide to the department of revenue a list of the qualifying employers
27 approved for a credit certificate, the qualifying new employees employed by the qualifying employer, and the
28 aggregate total of net employee growth and qualified net employee growth for qualified employers claiming the
